lxsession (0.4.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New option introduced since version 0.4:
    -e NAME	specify name of DE, such as LXDE, GNOME, or XFCE.

  If you gets crash during startup after upgrade from 0.3.8 to 0.4,
  you may hitting the same problem mentioned at #575961. You may need
  to specific the new option to avoid this problem.

 -- Andrew Lee (李健秋) <ajqlee@debian.org>  Sun, 11 Apr 2010 22:33:23 +0800
